description: A dense (nearly 500 pages) richly documented ultimate explorer's guide to more than 700 hidden marvels, events and curiosities around the world.

description: The last voyage of the Lusitania, the passenger liner sunk by a German torpedo in 1915; by the author of “The Devil in the White City.”

description: The story of the bicycle mechanics from Ohio who ushered in the age of flight.
title: THE WRIGHT BROTHERS

description: The author and his brother travel 2,000 miles by mule and wagon from Missouri to Oregon.

description: A biography of the Pacific Ocean.
